    "body": "@minaminao Oops not the `vm.chainId` is the `vm.sign`\r\n\r\nversion: forge 0.2.0 (e947899 2022-09-01T13:47:59.537286Z)\r\n\r\nerror message:\r\n```\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  Integer overflow when casting to u64\r\nLocation: $HOME/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/primitive-types-0.11.1/src/lib.rs:38\r\n```\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction testFuzzSet(uint256 chainId_, uint256 fuzzUint256_) external {\r\n    vm.chainId(chainId_);\r\n    (uint8 v, bytes32 r, bytes32 s) = vm.sign(pk, bytes32(fuzzUint256_)); // Panic here\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd it can be fixed if I use `uint64`\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction testFuzzSet(uint64 chainId_, uint256 fuzzUint256_) external {\r\n    vm.chainId(uint256(chainId_));\r\n    (uint8 v, bytes32 r, bytes32 s) = vm.sign(pk, bytes32(fuzzUint256_));\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
